r1632 | pedroix | 2011-02-13 21:12:37 -0600 (Sun, 13 Feb 2011) | 2 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/js/calendar.php

User preference hour format H which means hour with leading 0, was not being passed correctly to the Datetime Calendar format handler as HH.
So when a user typed manually a date with time, the time handler would complain if the user typed in the leading 0 of the hour.
